description.narrative: (Haiti): USAID's newly-awarded four-year Health Service Delivery project, also known as Project Santé, will provide increased access to the MOH-approved package of integrated primary health care services in Haiti's ten geographic departments. Project Santé supports primary health care service delivery in 164 health facilities nationwide. Services provided during this fiscal year will include pre and post-natal care, family planning, nutrition, child health services including immunization and nutrition, sanitation and hygiene and HIV services. With FY 2018 funds, in addition to providing services, the project will also provide staff training, integrated supervision and site management support to improve facilities' abilities to provide quality services. Expected results are improved health status of the Haitian population, including increased vaccination coverage, increased uptake of family planning services and improvements in coverage or maternal health and nutrition services. Expected outcomes also include more rigorous management practices at the facility and community levels, including improved management of human resources, leading to a strengthened capacity of the Ministry of Health to manage and monitor health service delivery..
